110.name: God Save The Key
110.description:
‚ÄúGod Save The Key‚Äù by artist YuYu takes a spin on renaissance masterpieces to humourlessly remind us the importance of self sovereignty - Not your Keys, Not your coins. YuYu's reinterpretation of Jacques-Louis David's painting The Oath of the Horatii (1786) draws inspiration from the three depicted brothers and their unity, reflecting the collective efforts of the web3 community to defend and uphold its ethos.   
   
Additionally, the artwork combines elements from Karl Brullov's The Last Day of Pompeii (1833), lighting with its eruption the left corner of the background, and Briton Riviere's lions from Daniel's Answer to the King (1892) encircle the main character, serving as indicators of imminent danger. Through these conceptual elements, the work depicts the turbulent nature of cryptocurrency while emphasizing the vital role of unity and collective action in fortifying decentralization.  
   
Artworks used:   
1. The Oath of the Horatii 1786 - Jacques-Louis David   
2. The Last Day of Pompeii 1833 - Karl Brullov   
3. Daniel's Answer To The King 1892 - Briton Riviere   
  
Meme: 10  
Season: 3

115.name: Vital Energy
115.description:
"Vital Energy" is a piece of art that captivates the imagination with its visual narrative and its emotive message. The protagonist of this story is a child named Jonny Boy, a curious and adventurous soul who transcends the limitations of reality.   
   
The artwork opens with Jonny Boy gracefully soaring amidst the clouds, arms spread wide like wings, his gaze filled with wonder and fear at the same time. This image symbolizes childhood, a time of discovery and uncertainty where every moment is a new adventure.   
   
However, the scene takes an unexpected turn when Jonny Boy is struck by a cascade of arrows materializing out of nowhere.  This detail emphasizes that even when Jonny Boy faces challenges and obstacles, he must maintain faith in himself and his journey. JonnyBoy represents each of us struggling and enduring to improve this difficult world.    
   
I dedicated this work to WAGMI because this phrase is magical, it unites people in a feeling of belonging and mutual support. When you say or share this acronym, you create a bond with others who share the same spirit of determination and confidence in the future.   
  
Meme: 2  
Season: 3  
Card: 3

119.name: Equilibrium
119.description:
In the heart of the abyss stands a monolith-like structure, representing a scale, a balance between both worlds with its "weights" extending on both sides.   
   
The left side, a vibrant depiction of nature unfolds, captivating the essence of real-life experiences and fundamental rights, evoking a connection to our physical world.   
   
The right side of the scale however, takes on a digital persona. This realm represents the realm of Digital Rights, where the virtual realm intertwines with our daily lives.   
   
We witness the delicate balance between real-world and digital rights, where one cannot exist without the other, emphasizing the imperative to value each sphere equally. A profound reminder that compromising either realm would undermine the harmonious coexistence of these vital aspects of our lives.   
   
TLDR; SEIZE THE RIGHTS OF DIGITALIZATION   
   
Meme: 11   
Season: 4

161.name: Ode to the Buidlers
161.description:
"Ode to the Buidlers" is a card created with a photographic technique known as "Photogrammetry." Photogrammetry involves scanning an areaand converting the photos and video into 3D points (aka point cloud). Those points are then rendered in a 3D program and editing, lighting, and other effects are added to create the final piece.

The entire process took around 2 months to complete, as I had to build the stage for the card. The hardest part was actually contacting the various buidlers in the space to ask for their permission to use their PFPs in the card. Some of the buidlers I was able to successfully contact were: 

1) Punk 6529  
2) Richerd - Manifold  
3) Pravjin - Deca  
4) Justin Trimble - Stability AI  
5) Ben Strauss - Transient Labs  
6) Snowfro - Artblocks  
7) Claire Silver - Accelerate Art  
8) Rayan - Oncyber  
9) Fonz - Tokenproof 
10) Norcalguy - ClickCreate

I was then able to order poster-sized prints of their PFPs. After obtaining the prints, I scouted for an area that fit my parameters for a successful scan. This part took me an entire day from morning until night. It is very difficult, because finding the perfect area will determine if the card will be loopable or not. Once I decided on the location, I came back on a different day, put up the posters, scanned the area, and then proceeded to the next month's work of editing and production. I also invested in a beefier video card for the sole purpose of creating this card.

I wanted to create a card that demonstrated my effort and dedication to the Memes. Not only high effort but also something new and different with a theme. The location this was shot at is Euljiro, Seoul, South Korea. This is an area where metal shop workers build components used in everyday machines and electronics. Not only that, but the sound recorded on the spot is also of the metal shop workers at their craft. And the PFPs are people who contribute to the web3 space with DApps we use in our everyday life.

Finally, the small blocks created through this technique can also be thought of as "The Buidler's Blocks."

PTS file - https://app.ardrive.io/#/file/f385ed97-e8e9-4559-ae23-7a5b1ce05de0/view  
PSX file - https://app.ardrive.io/#/file/fb5f7702-a2f8-4d88-ad5f-46de0281a9ac/view

165.name: Echoes of Fortitude
165.description:
A solitary figure navigates an abstract landscape, embodying the universal journey of endurance. A silhouette of unwavering strength moves amidst the shifting hues, embodying the intricate web of existence; survival is not a mere act of enduring, but a dynamic dance with life's challenges. It is the innate instinct to persist, adapt, and thrive amidst adversities. Yet, at the heart of this survival lies resilience‚Äîan extraordinary force that transcends mere existence. Resilience is the art of not just bouncing back from setbacks but thriving and growing through the crucible of trials. It transforms hardships into opportunities, embodying the profound strength to navigate through the storms of life, emerge stronger, and continue the relentless pursuit of continuity with unwavering fortitude. In this symbiotic relationship, survival and resilience become intertwined threads, weaving a narrative of indomitable spirit and the transformative power of overcoming.

Now in the open metaverse we can construct and experience worlds that mirror the grandeur and communal spirit of the ancient Parthenon, blending timeless human creativity with the limitless possibilities of the digital. Old underpins new and heralds our digital future.

177.name: STOP GM
177.description:
Protestors are trying to Stop GM from being in museums. This latest protest shows pink wojaks holding up a multi-media device expressing their hate for all things Web3, NFT, GM, Pepe, Cryptoart, Freedom To Transact & more. The 2 distressed Wojaks entered the Museum Of CryptoArt in Washington, DC at approximately 4:20pm on November 11, 2026 and threw Bitcoin colored paint on the GM meme by Punk 6529. The hand drawn characters looked malnourished and smelled of urine, while wearing STOP GM Shirts. They threw the paint and then proceeded to super glue themselves to the MOCA's walls. "GM" by Rare Scrilla, an onchain piece of music created in 2021, using Arpeggi Labs onchain DAW plays while DJPEPE overseas the drama and later expressed, "I wouldn't steal nobody's girls who act like that, dawg."

The sunflower rising from the magma embodies hope, reminding us that life can sprout from unexpected places, bringing a new cycle of prosperity.

By seizing the memes of production we find brotherhood, pleasure, and the concerted gusto to change the system, empowered in solidarity. Memes are the catalyst for our revolution to achieve self sovereignty. 
‚ÄúCarpe GM‚Äù, 2024 by Rebecca Rose. 3D digital Collage, dimensions: 1080x1080 at 155.4mb, duration: 0:52.

This piece is the 6529 Meme Card Collection's season 6 finale, and is part of the artist‚Äôs ongoing series ‚ÄúDeepCuts‚Äù, 3D collages with depth inspired by songs. The soundtrack is edited by the artist and contains excerpts from ‚ÄúCaptain Shepherd‚Äôs Quickstep, a public domain piece from 1850 recorded by the Library of Congress in 1974. Musical citation: Grafulla, Claudio S., composer. Fennell, Frederick, conductor. ‚ÄúCaptain Shepherd‚Äôs Quickstep.‚Äù Sound recording. Washington, DC: The Library of Congress Recording Laboratory, September 1974. From Library of Congress, Our Musical Past. Real Audio, mp3. https://www.loc.gov/item/cwband.recs005/ (accessed February 29, 2024).

Rebecca Rose is an award winning collage artist exploring collaged sculpts and holograms. Her 20+ year body of analog, sculptural, and digital collage has received multiple major artist grants co-sponsored by The Robert Rauschenberg Foundation, The Andy Warhol Foundation, The Joan Mitchell Foundation, The Willem de Kooning Foundation, The Andrew Mellon Foundation, The Ford Foundation, and Bloomberg Philanthropic.

230.name: The Suits
230.description:
The artwork portrays a deeper meaning of the invasion of traditional financial institutions, clarifying the clash between traditional finance and cryptocurrency, personified by the protagonist's struggle against encroaching "suits." The loud warning of "The suits are coming" underscores the threat of institutional control, especially with the recent approval of Bitcoin ETFs.

As the protagonist traverses through blockchain networks, defending their cryptocurrency holdings, the piece emphasizes the need for autonomy against regulation. The journey through different eras symbolizes the volatility of the crypto market, highlighting the challenges investors face.

The scene featuring Gary Gensler's head atop a gigantic robot commanding an army of suits serves as a playful and exaggerated (or not) representation of the regulatory authority's involvement in the cryptocurrency space.

The final revelation of staged visual effects not only underscores the need to discern reality from illusion but also serves as a cautionary tale against scams and false narratives in the crypto space.

241.name: A Symphony in Chaos
241.description:
In the ancient city of Lumen, where power was once tightly held by the elite, a quiet revolution began. Satoshi, a visionary, dreamed of a world where everyone could transact freely. His creation, the blockchain, spread like wildfire. The Apes, wise guardians, taught the masses to seize the memes of production, transforming the cityscape into a symbol of collective strength.

A rocket soared to the moon, embodying their shared aspirations, while a majestic bull balanced coins and keys, guarding the newfound freedom. Amidst this, the Statue of Liberty held a ledger, symbolizing the dawn of decentralization. At the heart of Lumen, 6529 held a ledger encircled by angels, illuminating the power of community and hope. A powerful fist tattooed with ""JPEG"" emerged from the earth, symbolizing the emerging power of the people. In this tale of freedom, the true strength of Lumen lay in the hands of its people, united and empowered by their collective dream.

**100 = CENTURY, a representation of a hundred years, suggesting longevity and endurance.  
**100 = The Roman numeral C, signifying "complete" or "closed loop," indicating wholeness or unity.

269.name: Place All Your Bets
269.description:
"Scared Money Don't Make Money" - Billy Napier

I've always viewed life as a game of predictions, calculations, and a final reliance on luck. "Place All Your Bets" embodies this mindset, encouraging you to bet on yourself and reach the high-stakes tables where the real game begins.

The artwork portrays a casino scene filled with familiar faces, reflecting the web3 art community ‚Äî a world where grit is essential for survival. At the center stands the devil‚Äôs advocate, grinning despite not knowing the second card, confident in his house edge. Yet, the other players share the same smile, understanding the game and thus leveling the playing field.

This piece captures the thrill and adrenaline of "The Game," where participants must analyze, predict, and hope for luck to win big. They are here because they love the game. So, "Place All Your Bets," but remember ‚Äî never split 10s.

274.name: Seize the Digital Bloom
274.description:
"Seize the Digital Bloom" plunges viewers into a vivid, surrealist world where the boundaries between digital culture and nature dissolve. In this striking landscape, memes break free from their online confines, flowering into potent symbols of societal change. At its center, a retro television commands attention with the rebellious call to "Seize the Memes of Production," signaling a paradigm shift in how we create and consume digital content. A frog, poised in meditation beside a tranquil pool, represents the calm within the digital storm, embodying the zen-like balance required to navigate this new frontier. Around it, human-like flowers bloom, merging organic beauty with technological artifice, illustrating the harmonious chaos of our interconnected world. This artwork encapsulates the dizzying blend of the mundane and the profound, where the digital and the natural coexist in a vibrant, ever-evolving dance of memes, technology, and boundless creativity.

277.name: Rise
277.description:
In a world where everything is crumbling where signs of defeat, despair, and destruction loom large 
We stand resolute. The vibrant neon lights, once symbols of hope and prosperity, now flicker in flames, mirroring the chaos that surrounds them. Broken tools, shattered dreams, and discarded art lie strewn across the ground, yet the figure remains unyielding. 

With a paintbrush in hand and determination in their eyes, they refuse to give up. The cracks in their resolve are evident, but they are the marks of resilience, not weakness. The key to survival is not in avoiding the fall but in rising from the ruins, time and time again. This is a testament to the spirit that never surrenders, even when the world is ablaze. 

Survival is not just about staying alive; it‚Äôs about facing the inferno and choosing to fight back, with creativity as both the weapon and the shield.

281.name: Philosopher's Bitcoin
281.description:
"Philosopher's Bitcoin" is a meme representing the journey of discovering the ultimate key to the perfect cryptocurrency ‚Äî a recipe for both financial and spiritual enlightenment. It symbolizes the modern-day alchemist's quest to unlock a secret formula for growth in both realms. This meme is said to bring luck in trading.

This concept draws inspiration from alchemy, specifically the Philosopher's Stone and the Rebis. The central figure combines both male and female elements, symbolizing the reconciliation of opposites ‚Äî spirit and matter, logic and emotion. The meme is adorned with cryptographic symbols and blockchain-inspired patterns.

Philosopher's Bitcoin aligns with the "Freedom to Transact" theme. "The Search for the Perfect Coin" emphasizes how cryptocurrency serves as the vehicle for achieving this freedom, facilitating transactions without barriers and enabling individuals to exercise control over their financial interactions.

For context, alchemy aimed at both material and spiritual transformation. Practically, alchemists sought to transmute base metals into gold, discover the Philosopher's Stone ‚Äî a substance that enables transmutation and grants immortality ‚Äî and develop early forms of medicine. Spiritually, alchemy was about personal transformation, mirroring the process of purifying the soul through stages of growth. It also sought to reconcile opposites like spirit and matter, male and female, light and dark, to achieve balance.

The Rebis (from the Latin res bina, meaning "dual matter") is the end product of the alchemical magnum opus or Great Work. After undergoing stages of decay and purification, opposing qualities are separated and then reunited in what is often described as the divine hermaphrodite ‚Äî a reconciliation of spirit and matter. This being embodies both male and female aspects, as symbolized by a single body with two heads, one male and one female.

Details like an embroidery of a unicorn, referencing Uniswap, and the planet Jupiter, symbolizing Solana traders, are incorporated to give nods to key elements in the crypto world. A gecko or salamander is also present, symbolizing both fire in alchemy and CoinGecko in crypto. These small symbols represent what makes a great trader ‚Äî wisdom, foresight, and a deep connection to the market. 

The number seven, present in the meme, holds significant symbolic importance in alchemy, especially in the context of the Rebis. In alchemical tradition, seven often represents the completion of a cycle, spiritual transformation, and the harmony of opposites. Alchemy associates seven classical planets with seven corresponding metals. The Sun (Sol) is associated with gold, symbolizing purity and enlightenment, while the Moon (Luna) is linked to silver, representing intuition and the feminine principle. Mercury (Mercurius) is tied to the metal mercury (quicksilver), symbolizing transformation and the union of spirit and matter. Venus corresponds to copper, symbolizing beauty and harmony, while Mars is linked to iron, representing strength and masculine energy. Jupiter is associated with tin, symbolizing wisdom and growth, and Saturn corresponds to lead, representing transformation and the base material to be purified. These seven elements must be harmonized and transmuted during the alchemical process.

283.name: post_apoXkalypse_summer.jPG
283.description:
post_apoXkalypse_summer.jPG is the title of an ode, a micro-story, a joke. 

Once upon a time, there was a polarised world in which its inhabitants were forced to choose their future from the cradle: technological or analogue, cultured or culturists, thinkers or clowns? They were aimless characters, without ideals or values. They were the copy of the copy of the copy of the copy of those who one day fought for their dreams, but without ink. Until one day our protagonist, tired of wandering among soulless skyscrapers, rebelled against the system and burned everything in his path, recruiting a 
legion of copies of copies of copies of those who were once the originals to establish a new social and economic order in which to be free. Be the original, not the copy. 

Burn it.  
Burn the past.  
Burn what hurts.  
Burn the pictures of your exes.  
Burn all your jpgs.  
You're through the worst.  

Post apocalypse will bring you health, money and love.

284.name: Pepemoto: The Genesis Revolution
284.description:
One of the world‚Äôs brightest minds fought for freedom and then disappeared. Satoshi Nakamoto, like some kind of digital superhero, created a decentralized world while concealing his identity, but unlike a movie, his story is real! In a world where every move can be tracked, Nakamoto‚Äôs every action unfolded before the eyes of the world. 

Pepemoto is the embodiment of this untold hero, depicted as a symbol of meme culture and the digital revolution. The final Genesis Block marks the end of his known legacy, but the beginning of a global transformation. If Bitcoin is a book constantly being written, then the Genesis Block is the first page ‚Äî inscribed with the sentence, "The Times 03/Jan/2009 Chancellor on brink of second bailout for banks." This cryptic message, hidden within the code, reflects a powerful stance against the flaws of the centralized financial systems. 

In this artwork, Pepemoto stands as a bridge between the cryptic genius of Satoshi and the meme culture of today, embodying rebellion, innovation, and freedom in the digital age. He is both a masked creator and a symbol of liberation, moving through the blockchain without leaving a trace yet forever altering the course of history. Pepemoto‚Äôs journey is not just a story of technology but a revolution ‚Äî the Genesis of a new era.

Satoshi Nakamoto, like some kind of digital superhero, created a decentralized world while concealing his identity, but unlike a movie, his story is real! In a world where every move can be tracked, Nakamoto‚Äôs every action unfolded before the eyes of the world. 

Pepemoto is the embodiment of this untold hero, depicted as a symbol of meme culture and the digital revolution. The final Genesis Block marks the end of his known legacy, but the beginning of a global transformation. If Bitcoin is a book constantly being written, then the Genesis Block is the first page ‚Äî inscribed with the sentence, "The Times 03/Jan/2009 Chancellor on brink of second bailout for banks." This cryptic message, hidden within the code, reflects a powerful stance against the flaws of the centralized financial systems. 

In this artwork, Pepemoto stands as a bridge between the cryptic genius of Satoshi and the meme culture of today, embodying rebellion, innovation, and freedom in the digital age. He is both a masked creator and a symbol of liberation, moving through the blockchain without leaving a trace yet forever altering the course of history. Pepemoto‚Äôs journey is not just a story of technology but a revolution ‚Äî the Genesis of a new era.

285.name: Here Lies
285.description:
This artwork critiques centralized power while celebrating the ideals of decentralization. The phrase ‚ÄúHic Situs Imperium Centrale‚Äù is a creative adaptation of the Latin epitaph ‚ÄúHic Situs Est,‚Äù meaning ‚ÄúHere Lies.‚Äù Traditionally found on Roman tombstones, it conveys finality and legacy. By adding ‚ÄúImperium Centrale‚Äù‚Äî‚ÄúCentral Power‚Äù‚Äîthe phrase symbolizes the burial of central authority, with the Roman Empire serving as a historical reference for such systems.

The tulip used in the composition resembles the Semper Augustus, the rarest and most valuable tulip in history. During the 17th-century Tulip Mania, it embodied wealth, greed, and colonial power. Although the original Semper Augustus is extinct, this tulip‚Äîfound in the garden of Toronto‚Äôs City Hall‚Äîadds a playful and rebellious twist, subtly reclaiming control from institutional authority.

The composition is carefully designed with shadows connecting each element‚Äîthe skull, vase, and tulip‚Äîcreating a visual loop that guides the viewer‚Äôs gaze. The skull represents mortality, the vase symbolizes the rigidity of authority, the tulip reflects the fragility of beauty and power, and the shadows emphasize the inevitable connection between these concepts. Through this thoughtful arrangement, the artwork critiques control systems while embracing transformation, impermanence, and decentralized freedom.

287.name: Meta(morphosis)
287.description:
Who are we really? In an ever-online world, our digital avatars often feel more authentic than our physical selves. Meta(morphosis) explores this, where digital identities take on lives of their own, sometimes feeling more real than the people behind the screens. Our true or ‚Äòdesired‚Äô personalities emerge more freely online, making digital rights crucial. The computer acts as a portal, not just a tool, enabling communities where anyone can belong. The painting shows the physical self as an observer, gazing at larger-than-life digital selves, questioning whether the physical is merely an extension.

289.name: Ruins of the Future
289.description:
Ruins of the Future is a digital art piece that visualizes the connection between ancient ruins, futuristic blockchain technology, and the freedom to transact. It features a futuristic, ruin-like temple surrounded by nature, symbolizing a world where decentralized technology has become the foundation of economic freedom. This combination of ancient architectural forms with futuristic elements reflects the idea that today's blockchain innovations‚Äîempowering individuals with the freedom to exchange value without intermediaries - will become the historical artifacts of tomorrow.

Just as we study ancient ruins to understand past civilizations, future generations will examine the blockchain era as a key moment in the evolution of economic freedom. The artwork serves as a reminder that we are collectively shaping the future's past, building the technological ruins that will inspire those who come after us, and empowering them with the ability to transact freely across borders and systems.

290.name: TAP TAP, Who's There?
290.description:
We should all be taking the necessary extra steps to keep our grails safe from scammers. ‚ÄúTAP TAP, Who‚Äôs There?‚Äù is a playful take on TAP, aka the Three Address Protocol by 6529. 

For this piece I wanted to portray the three wallet types (hot, warm and cold) as front doors, with scammers trying various ways to get into the cold wallets with no success, successfully getting into the warm wallets only to find iconic NFTs that are already being transferred, and successfully getting into the hot wallets to find nothing in there but posters and tumbleweed.

293.name: Started by Anon
293.description:
"Started by Anon‚Äù has a direct reference to the point that everyone has the right to act in the digital realm through anonymous identities, pseudonymous identities or software agents, as long as each person maintains personal responsibility for the actions of all their identities and agents. Many in the crypto community now operate under their own alternative identities promoting decentralized ownership and privacy. Be it the Bitcoin founder anonymous identity Satoshi Nakamoto, NFT Auctions started by anons on regular basis, or even the Meme Card that is started itself by 6529 who remains anon - the community is sinked with anonymity. 

The figure in the presented work is a strong representation of freedom. Being in space that's all about personal ownership, the person is anon, but is obviously not in the void, the person is interconnected with community and the community only strives when there are connections and unity, highlighting intellectual interchange.

294.name: Pepius Productiva Florenti
294.description:
Way back at the start of the industrial revolution, there was a curious moment when the old and the new collided. Advertisements showcasing the wonders of new technology borrowed design elements that people found appealing from the previous era. We ended up with images of printing presses, sewing machines, tractors, and locomotives surrounded by flowers and decorative patterns, as if these machines were our new queens and kings.

We find ourselves in a similar era of transition now. As technologies shift rapidly around us, we hold on to the past. We use the visual language we're familiar with to express the beauty of what‚Äôs to come. This artwork is a nod to a previous era of technological innovation and change. Here, we see the ‚ÄúPepius Productiva Florentia‚Äù blossoming from the rich soil seeded by cryptocurrencies‚Äîcurrencies that laid a foundation for many of us to step into this new world and flourish. And of course, they‚Äôve sprouted bright new iterations of the symbols we rely on for comfort along the way.
